  <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I tried visually replacing a few <a href="/card/logseq/">card/Logseq</a> tags with icons in CSS. It worked!</p>
<p><figure>
    <img src="/../../../attachments/img/2022-08-04-logseq-icons.png" alt="attachments/img/2022-08-04-logseq-icons.png"/></figure>
Three down, a few thousand to go</p>
<p>How&rsquo;d I do it? Here I&rsquo;ll just paste from my journal note figuring out the first one. I&rsquo;m sure I&rsquo;ll revisit this tonight after taking care of the day&rsquo;s business.</p>
<ul>
<li>#idea Thinking about custom tag icons for logseq
<ul>
<li>#warning under construction #warning</li>
<li>Inspired by Obsidian <a href="https://publish.obsidian.md/hub/02&#43;-&#43;Community&#43;Expansions/02.05&#43;All&#43;Community&#43;Expansions/CSS&#43;Snippets/Alternate&#43;Checkboxes&#43;%28SlRvb%29">Alternate Checkboxes</a> CSS snippet</li>
<li>Here&rsquo;s what <code>#idea</code> looks like in the dev console:</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<figure class="highlight">
  <pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"
    ><code class="language-html" data-lang="html"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">div</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">   <span class="na">class</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&#34;&#34;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">   <span class="na">style</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&#34;display: inline;&#34;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">   <span class="na">data-tooltipped</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&#34;&#34;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">   <span class="na">aria-describedby</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&#34;tippy-tooltip-119&#34;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">   <span class="na">data-original-title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&#34;null&#34;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">   <span class="p">&gt;&lt;</span><span class="nt">a</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">	   <span class="na">data-ref</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&#34;idea&#34;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">	   <span class="na">class</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&#34;tag&#34;</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>#idea<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">a</span><span class="p">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="nt">div</span><span class="p">&gt;</span></span></span></code></pre>
</figure><ul>
<li>#question how do my installed plugins change the structure?
<ul>
<li>I don&rsquo;t think I currently have any plugins that alter element attributes</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Set up <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Selectors">CSS Selector</a> #bookmark to match
<ul>
<li><code>a.tag[data-ref=&quot;idea&quot;]</code></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Hide the displayed tag by making it tiny</li>
</ul>
<figure class="highlight">
  <pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"
    ><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nt">a</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nc">tag</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="nt">data-ref</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&#34;idea&#34;</span><span class="o">]</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">	<span class="k">border</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="kc">none</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">	<span class="k">font-size</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">}</span></span></span></code></pre>
</figure><ul>
<li>Append an icon with the font size we started at</li>
</ul>
<figure class="highlight">
  <pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"
    ><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nt">a</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nc">tag</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="nt">data-ref</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&#34;idea&#34;</span><span class="o">]</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nd">after</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">	<span class="k">content</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">&#34;ðŸ’¡&#34;</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">	<span class="k">font-size</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="kc">initial</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">}</span></span></span></code></pre>
</figure><ul>
<li>as-is, this has accessibility issues and <code>font-size: initial</code> won&rsquo;t work with headings. Also, to do it right I should be encoding the icon</li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>
